attributes/title: Abandoned brick house, site of Yellow Medicine Agency, near Granite Falls, Minnesota
attributes/description_ts/attributes/val: Abandoned brick house located at the site of the Yellow Medicine Agency. The Yellow Medicine Agency was destroyed during the Dakota Conflict of 1852, and the site is now part of Upper Sioux Agency State Park in Minnesota. This image is by Arthur Adams, Minneapolis high school teacher, local historian, and photographer. Adams traveled throughout Minnesota, taking photographs to augment his lectures. His studio was located at 3648 Lyndale Avenue South in Minneapolis.

attributes/title: A campsite at the Annual White Earth Celebration and Pow Wow, White Earth, Minnesota
attributes/description_ts/attributes/val: Unidentified Ojibwe women are at a campsite. They are seated on the ground in front of a tent with cooking pots, dishes, and jars between them; there are buckets in the foreground. This snapshot by Stella Stocker is from her photograph album. Stocker, a musician and music educator, studied American Indian music among the Ojibwe people in Minnesota.
attributes/contributing_organization_tes: University of Minnesota Duluth, Kathryn A. Martin Library, University Archives
